Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}; dice half into 1-inch pieces and grate the other half on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Peel and dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and dice @carrot{3%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and cut into 1-inch pieces.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine chicken, half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Stir to coat chicken; set aside to marinate.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and 1 tsp salt.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat (large #pot{} for 4 servings). Stir in garlic, grated onion, @garam masala{1%tsp}, @turmeric{1/4%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. (You'll use more turmeric later.) Cook, stirring, until golden brown and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Add a few splashes of water if onion starts to brown too quickly.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} and @water{1/2%cup}. Stir and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a medium simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> When sauce is ready to have chicken added, a light sheen of oil will rise to the top.

Stir in chicken with marinade and cilantro; simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Turmeric Rice ==

While chicken is cooking, in a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings), combine @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, @turmeric{1/2%tsp}, and a large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Potatoes & Carrot ==

While chicken and rice cook, in a #large microwave-safe bowl{}, combine potatoes, carrot, and @salt{1%tsp}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until potatoes and carrot are tender, ~{6%minutes}.

In a #large pan{}, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} and @butter{1/2%tablespoon} over medium-high heat. Add potatoes and carrot, diced onion, half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, remaining @turmeric{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are golden brown and have formed a crust, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Squeeze juice from one lemon wedge over potatoes and carrot. Taste and season with salt if needed.

== To Serve ==

Stir remaining sour cream into curry.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice, curry, and potatoes and carrot between plates or #bowls{}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.